<p><b>Tobias Jonathan Ansell Wolff</b> (born June 19, 1945, in <a href="/wiki/Birmingham,_Alabama" title="Birmingham, Alabama">Birmingham</a>, <a href="/wiki/Alabama" title="Alabama">Alabama</a>) is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Author" title="Author">author</a>.</p>
<p>He is best known for his <a href="/wiki/Short_stories" title="Short stories" class="mw-redirect">short stories</a> and his <a href="/wiki/Memoirs" title="Memoirs" class="mw-redirect">memoirs</a>, although he has written two <a href="/wiki/Novels" title="Novels" class="mw-redirect">novels</a> (most recently <i><a href="/wiki/Old_School_(novel)" title="Old School (novel)">Old School</a></i>).</p>
